Package lib.interfaces

Interface ListADT<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of elements maintained by this list
All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
All Known Subinterfaces:
OrderedListADT<T>, UnorderedListADT<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayList, ArrayOrderedList, ArrayUnorderedList, CircularDoubleLinkedList, DoubleLinkedOrderedList, DoubleLinkedUnorderedList, LinkedList, LinkedOrderedList, LinkedUnorderedList
public interface ListADT<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
A generic interface representing the abstract data type for a list. A list is an ordered collection that allows duplicate elements and supports positional access and modifications.
